# JavaScript Practice in Exercises for Programmers

## Challenge 1 - Saying Hello

### Goal
Create a program that prompts for your name and prints a greeting using your name

### Inputs
name

### Outputs
greetingMessage

### Pseudocode
Prompt for name with "What is your name?"

Concatentate name into greetingMessage "Hello name, nice to meet you!"

Display updated greetingMessage that includes name


***

## Challenge 2 - Counting the Number of Characters

### Goal
Create a program that prompts for an input string and dis- plays output that shows the input string and the number of characters the string contain

### Inputs
inputString

### Outputs
charCount

### Pseudocode
Prompt for inputString with "What is the input string?"

Count characters for inputString using built-in function

Display message with inputString and charCount - "inputString has charCount characters."


***

## Challenge 3 - Printing Quotes

### Goal
Create a program that prompts for a quote and an author. Display the quotation and author as shown in the example output

### Inputs
quoteString
authorName

### Outputs
finalMessage

### Pseudocode
Prompt for quoteString with "What is the quote?"
Prompt for authorName with "Who said it?"

Contatenate finalMessage with "authorName says, "quoteString."" (using escape characters)

Display finalMessage


***

## Challenge 4 - Mad Lib

### Goal
Create a simple mad-lib program that prompts for a noun, a verb, an adverb, and an adjective and injects those into a story that you create

### Inputs
inputNoun
inputVerb
inputAdverb
inputAdjective

### Outputs
finalMessage

### Pseudocode
Prompt for inputNoun with "Enter a noun:"
Prompt for inputVerb with "Enter a verb:"
Prompt for inputAdverb with "Enter a adverb:"
Prompt for inputAdjective with "Enter a adjective:"

Contatenate finalMessage with "Do you inputVerb your inputAdjective inputNoun inputAdjective? That's hilarious!"

Display finalMessage


***

## Challenge 5 - Simple Math

### Goal
Write a program that prompts for two numbers. Print the sum, difference, product, and quotient of those numbers as shown in the example output

### Inputs
firstNum
secondNum

### Outputs
sumEquation
differenceEquation
productEquation
quotientEquation

### Pseudocode
Prompt for firstNum with "What is the first number?"
Prompt for secondNum with "What is the second number?"

Convert firstNum to number format
Convert secondNum to number format

Concatenate sumEquation with firstNum "+" secondNum "=" (firstNum + secondNum)
Concatenate differenceEquation with firstNum "-" secondNum "=" (firstNum - secondNum)
Concatenate productEquation with firstNum "*" secondNum "=" (firstNum * secondNum)
Concatenate quotientEquation with firstNum "/" secondNum "=" (firstNum / secondNum) and rounding to the nearest hundredth

Display sumEquation, differenceEquation, productEquation, and quotientEquation altogether with line breaks


***

## Challenge 6 - Retirement Calculator

### Goal
Create a program that determines how many years you have left until retirement and the year you can retire. It should prompt for your current age and the age you want to retire and display the output as shown in the example that follows

### Inputs
currentAge
retireAgeGoal

### Outputs
yearsLeft
retireYear
finalMessage

### Pseudocode
Prompt for currentAge with "What is your current age?"
Prompt for retireAgeGoal with "At what age would you like to retire?"

Convert currentAge to number format
convert retireAgeGoal to number format

Calculate yearsLeft with retireAgeGoal - currentAge
Calculate retireYear with currentYear (built-in function) + yearsLeft

Concatenate finalMessage with "You have yearsLeft years left until you can retire. It's currentYear, so you can retire in retireYear." with line break between sentences.

Display finalmessage


***

## Challenge 7 - Area of a Rectangular Room

### Goal
Create a program that calculates the area of a room. Prompt the user for the length and width of the room in feet. Then display the area in both square feet and square meters

### Inputs
roomLength
roomWidth

### Assumptions
conversionConstant = 0.09290304

### Outputs
areaSqft
areaSqm
confirmationMessage
finalMessage

### Pseudocode
Prompt for roomLength in feet with "What is the length of the room in feet?"
Prompt for roomWidth in feet with "What is the width of the room in feet?"

Declare conversionConstant

Convert roomLength to number format
convert roomWidth to number format

Calculate areaSqft with roomLength * roomWidth
Calculate areaSqm with areaSqft * conversionConstant and round to 3 decimal places

Concatenate confirmationMessage with "You entered dimensions of roomLength feet by roomWidth feet."
Concatenate finalMessage with "The area is (line break) areaSqft square feet (line break) areaSqm square meters"

Display confirmationMessage
Display finalMessage


***

## Challenge 8 - Pizza Party

### Goal
Write a program to evenly divide pizzas. Prompt for the number of people, the number of pizzas, and the number of slices per pizza. Ensure that the number of pieces comes out even. Display the number of pieces of pizza each person should get. If there are leftovers, show the number of leftover pieces

### Inputs
countPeople
countPizzas

### Assumptions
slicesPerPizza = 12?

### Outputs
slicesPerPerson
slicesLeftover
confirmationMessage
finalMessage

### Pseudocode
Prompt for countPeople with "How many people?"
Prompt for countPizzas with "How many pizzas do you have?"

Declare slicesPerPizza

Convert countPeople to number format
convert countPizzas to number format

Calculate totalSlices with countPizzas * slicesPerPizza
Calculate slicesPerPerson with totalSlices / countPeople, rounded down
Calculate slicesLeftover with totalSlices - (countPeople * slicesPerPerson)

Concatenate confirmationMessage with "countPeople people with countPizzas pizzas"
Concatenate finalMessage with "Each person gets slicesPerPerson slices of pizza. (line break) There are slicesLeftover leftover pieces."

Display confirmationMessage
Display finalMessage


***

## Challenge 9 - Paint Calculator

### Goal
Calculate gallons of paint needed to paint the ceiling of a room. Prompt for the length and width, and assume one gallon covers 350 square feet. Display the number of gallons needed to paint the ceiling as a whole number

### Inputs
ceilingLength
ceilingWidth

### Assumptions
gallonCoverage = 350 (1 gallon of paint covers 350 sq ft)

### Outputs
paintGallons
finalMessage

### Pseudocode
Prompt for ceilingLength with "What is the room length (in feet)?"
Prompt for ceilingWidth with "What is the room length (in feet)?"

Convert ceilingLength to number format
convert ceilingWidth to number format

Calculate ceilingArea with ceilingLength * ceilingWidth
Calculate paintGallons with ceilingArea / gallonCoverage, rounding up to the nearest whole number

Concatenate finalMessage with "You will need to purchase pantGallons gallons of paint to cover ceilingArea square feet."

Display finalMessage


***

## Challenge 10 - Self-Checkout

### Goal
Create a simple self-checkout system. Prompt for the prices and quantities of three items. Calculate the subtotal of the items. Then calculate the tax using a tax rate of 5.5%. Print out the line items with the quantity and total, and then print out the subtotal, tax amount, and total

### Inputs
price1
quantity1
price2
quantity2
price3
quantity3

### Assumptions
taxRate = 0.0055

### Outputs
subTotal
tax
finalTotal
finalMessage

### Pseudocode
Prompt for price1 with "Enter the price of item 1:"
Prompt for quantity1 with "Enter the quantity of item 1:"
Prompt for price2 with "Enter the price of item 1:"
Prompt for quantity2 with "Enter the quantity of item 1:"
Prompt for price3 with "Enter the price of item 1:"
Prompt for quantity3 with "Enter the quantity of item 1:"

Convert all values to number format

Calculate subTotal with "(price1 * quantity1) +
(price2 * quantity2) + (price3 * quantity3)
Calculate tax with subTotal * taxRate
Calculate finalTotal with subTotal + tax

Format subTotalPretty, taxPretty, and finalTotalPretty by adding $ and rounding to 2 decimal places

Concatenate finalMessage with "Subtotal: subTotalPretty (line break) Tax: taxPretty (line break) Total: finalTotalPretty"

Display finalMessage






